bdglue2.utility.schemadef

Class Format

  • java.lang.Object
    • bdglue2.utility.schemadef.Format
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    FormatAvro, FormatCassandra, FormatHiveAvro, FormatNoSQL

    public abstract class Format
extends Object
    Base class for the schema formaters that we support. This is abstract and must be extended.

      • top

        public abstract void top(String schema,
                         String table,
                         boolean noDoc)
                  throws IOException
        Format the "top" portion of the output file.
        Parameters:
        schema - the name of the schema that contains the table we are working with
        table - the name of the table we are working with
        noDoc - don't generate the doc field. This is specific to avro, and a hack needed to avoid a schema incompaitibiliy issue in the Hive SerDe if the old schema did not also have the doc field.
        Throws:
        IOException - if a JSON encoding issue occurs

        Format the fields that make up the "middle" of the output file.
        Parameters:
